headline: Why GE HealthCare (GEHC) Stock Is Up Today
summary: Shares of healthcare technology company GE HealthCare Technologies (NASDAQ:GEHC) jumped 2.8% in the afternoon session after the company announced a new distribution agreement for its cardiac imaging agent and received FDA clearance for an innovative CT imaging system.

headline: GE HealthCare Enters an Agreement to Distribute Flyrcado Through CDL Nuclear Technologies Group, a Leading Provider of Cardiac PET Imaging Equipment and Services in the U.S.

headline: GEHC Stock Gains Following Launch of Revolution Vibe CT Imaging System
summary: GE HealthCare's FDA-cleared Revolution Vibe CT promises faster, AI-driven cardiac imaging with improved clarity, boosting efficiency and patient comfort.
